# Phase 10 — Agent service keys. Plaintext credentials. NEVER commit.
# These files hold long-lived `omni_sk_*` tokens that the omni-agent
# trades at boot for a 15-min `kind: "agent"` JWT via
# `rust-work-service /api/v1/agent-identity/exchange`. Each Citrix box
# gets its own per-agent key — sharing or distributing them via git
# would leak production credentials and short-circuit the per-agent
# audit trail (`agent_service_keys.last_used_at`, the
# `agent_service_key.exchanged` tracing event). See
# `memorybank/OmniFrame/Implementations/Implement-Phase10-Service-Key-First-Rollout.md`
# §"Repository hygiene" for the operator-side pairing.
agent_service_key.txt
*.agent_service_key.txt
omni_sk_*.txt
.omniframe/
